duck: Quantum flux parametron - Invented by Eiichi Goto at the University of Tokyo, the Quantum Flux Parametron (QFP) is an improvement over his earlier parametron based digital logic technology.
A QFP or Quad Flat Package is a surface mount integrated circuit package with "gull wing" leads extending from each of the four sides.
Chip carrier - In electronics, a chip carrier is one of several kinds of surface mount technology packages for integrated circuits.
Pin grid array An alternative integrated circuit pin arrangement design
